<html>
  <head>
    <script src="script.js"></script>
  </head>

  <body>
    <canvas id="canvas"></canvas>
  </body>
</html>
```

**Explanation:**

* The program creates a variable `isDrawing` to track whether the user is currently drawing.
* It also creates variables `x` and `y` to store the mouse position.
* When the user clicks the mouse, the `mousedown` event listener is triggered, setting `isDrawing` to `true` and storing the mouse position in `x` and `y`.
* While the user is drawing, the `mousemove` event listener is triggered, drawing a line from the previous mouse position to the current position.
* When the user releases the mouse button, the `mouseup` event listener is triggered, setting `isDrawing` to `false`.

**Note:**

* You need to include the `script.js` file in your HTML document.
* You can change the canvas size in the HTML code.
* You can customize the line color and thickness in the JavaScript code.

